rComments: Great prof. He really cares about students' success, emphasizing learning rather than regurgitation. We had no exams although the 4 quizzes were each worth 10% but all open book, and the rest was writing your paper. His lectures were always organized and engaging and he's the kind of prof who doesn't believe in stupid questions. Highly recommend.

Brandon teaches you a lot. I appreciate that, but it was a tough class. He marks quickly. His passion for language is obvious. The only real issue I had was that the tests were generally fairly difficult and many of the answers weren't discussed in class. -- although they were in the readings -- so basically, you have to study everything.

It's clear Brandon Fry is very interested in linguistics & knows the subject well which is awesome. He was unclear about expectations with homework assignments & tests were much harder than what students were shown in class. Also, the DGDs were unorganized & there were times where we were taught incorrect concepts which is unfair and confusing.

Brandon Fry tries hard. Although he cares a lot about the subject and students, it's very hard to get a good grade. The DGD's were not well run. The questions on the tests are much harder than the examples given in class. You must try very hard if you want to even pass. Not an easy credit at all.

Brandon  s'assure d'avoir une bonne correspondance avec ses étudiants. Il communique souvent au travers de Blackboard et du courriel uottawa. Il structure bien ses classes et si un concept n'est pas clair, il s'assure de prendre le temps nécessaire pour éclaircir la matière. Un prof approchable et excellent!

He's super helpful and is very happy to answer your emails (quickly!) and to make time to meet if you need help with any concept. He knows that the book is pretty unclear at times so he really makes up for it in class. Very organized. His exams are pretty tough tho, although the 4 homework tasks that he gives definitely help to get a good cushion
super nice guy, always there to help but his tests are tough. needs a bit more teaching experience since it was his first year teaching but all in all a good prof with great potential.

This is the first year Mr. Fry is teaching and it doesn't show at all!  He is always very organized, doesn't give too much to read, and simplifies everything so that it's almost impossible NOT to understand. The manual is sometimes unclear, but the teacher is aware of that and compensates.  Easy pass if you study.  Best prof EVER.

He is a very good prof. He is clear and explains well but his exams are tough. During the lectures and the DGDs he will give you easy exercises but then in the exams the questions are very different and difficult so you have to use your logic or guess the answer. Make sure you understand everything very well - not a lot of things to know by heart.
